  <summary date="2019-02-07T19:53:25Z" status="Passed House">Preventing Crimes Against Veterans Act of 2019

This bill establishes a new criminal offense for knowingly executing, or attempting to execute, a scheme to defraud an individual of veterans' benefits. A violator is subject to criminal penalties&#8212;a fine, a prison term of up to five years, or both.</summary>
